## 📁 Project Structure

```
research-agent/
├── research_agent.py        # Agent code
├── README.md                # This file
├── brief/
│   └── AGENT_BRIEF.md       # Phase 1 — Problem, persona, I/O spec, risks
├── design/
│   └── DESIGN_DOC.md        # Phase 2 — Architecture, prompts, configuration
├── evals/
│   └── EVAL_SCORECARD.md    # Phase 4 — Test cases, rubric, failure modes
└── ops/
    └── OPS_RUNBOOK.md       # Phase 5 — Security, cost, observability, upgrades
```

The `/brief`, `/design`, `/evals`, and `/ops` folders document the full lifecycle of how this agent was designed and evaluated — not just what it does, but *why* it's built the way it is.

